PIK Group GDRs Surge Most Since May After Readmission in London

-- B y   J a s o n   C o r c o r a n
-- 
2011-03-15T16:11:50Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-03-15/pik-group-gdrs-surge-most-since-may-after-readmission-in-london.html
  PIK Group (PIKK) ’s global depository shares
jumped by their most since May after the company’s equity was
readmitted to the London Stock Exchange today.  The stock added 12 percent to $5.00 by 3:45 p.m. in London
trading.  The Moscow Arbitration Court lifted a Feb. 11 freeze order
on the company’s GDRs yesterday. Its GDRS were suspended by the
U.K.’s Financial Services Authority on Feb. 11.  PIK Group’s stock dropped 6 percent to 128.29 rubles by the
6:45 p.m. close in Moscow trading, for a decrease of 1.4 percent
since the freeze order.  To contact the reporter on this story:
